s in the sample compatible with being M4\ndwarfs. We obtained a good agreement between the stellar parameters computed\nwith VOSA and the estimations from observed spectra, also when comparing with\nan independent sample from the literature. The distribution of masses obtained\nwith VOSA is concentrated toward the very low-mass regime. Eight objects\npresent values of RUWE >= 1.4 and seven are consistent with being part of a\nbinary system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Mar 2022 23:03:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-04"}
